  "observations": [
    "Single-role model: ownerEverything — no multi-user permission surface, all data is local-first owner-data",
    "Three orthogonal navigation surfaces over the same Notes: file-tree (folders), wiki-links (backlinks), tags (nested)",
    "File-tree as primary structure (left sidebar) — folders are first-class, unlike Notion's page-as-database model",
    "Tabs at top mirror Chrome-style multi-document UX; each tab carries its own view mode (source/live-preview/reading)",
    "View mode is per-tab state (source/live-preview/reading) — a tri-state toggle, not a global setting",
    "Wiki-link [[Note Name]] auto-completes via fuzzy search and creates the note on click if missing — link-as-creation affordance",
    "Backlinks panel (right sidebar) shows incoming references with paragraph-context snippets",
    "Unlinked mentions surfaced as suggestions to linkify — separate from resolved backlinks",
    "Tags support nesting via #area/work syntax — hierarchical tag tree as a secondary navigation",
    "Aliases declared in YAML front-matter participate in wiki-link resolution (one note, many addressable names)",
    "Graph view has two scopes: global (force-directed over entire vault) and local (1-2 hop neighborhood per note)",
    "Graph filter chips (tags, paths, orphans, attachments) and color groups (tag/folder/regex) — exploration-mode UI",
    "Daily notes are template-driven, date-keyed (yyyy-mm-dd.md), surfaced via Calendar plugin in calendar grid",
    "Plugin ecosystem (1500+ community plugins) is the primary extensibility surface — Browse → install → enable workflow",
    "Themes are CSS-variable-based (200+) — purely cosmetic layer separate from functional plugins",
    "Cmd+O quick switcher (file-by-name fuzzy) and Cmd+Shift+F full-text (regex, scope, filters) are two distinct search modes",
    "Search-in-search compositional queries: 'tag:#ml file:research' — query DSL surface",
    "Sync is opt-in and provider-pluggable (Obsidian Sync E2EE / iCloud / Dropbox / Syncthing / Git) — vault is just a folder",
    "Publish is selective per-note (checkbox-driven) → static site at yourname.obsidian.page",
    "Markdown files are the single source of truth — UI is a derived view over plain-text files (local-first)",
    "Drag-to-reparent in file explorer is the primary move-to-folder affordance",
    "Workspaces capture full layout state (open tabs, panel positions) — saveable presets for context-switching"
  ]
}